Built in Lined and Graph Paper Backgrounds Now With Retina Graphics Optimized for iOS 6 Bug Fixes and Performance Enhancements Note: If you are running iOS 5 on an iPad 3 retina display you should upgrade to iOS 6 before installing this update. We re aware of an Apple bug that prevents our pen tool from working properly in iOS 5 on the retina iPad. Apple has fixed this bug in iOS 6.

NOTE: If you have version 1.2 installed we recommend that you do not install version 1.2.1 but wait for version 1.2.2 to become available. If you are installing for the first time or upgrading from version 1.1 or older you can go ahead and install 1.2.1 without any problems. For v1.2 users we are aware of a bug that will temporarily prevent your saved lessons from playing back properly on the iPad. We have fixed the issue and are waiting for Apple to approve our fix. If you ve been affected by this bug fear not! Your saved lessons will begin playing back normally on the iPad when you upgrade to v1.2.2 which will be available shortly. We re very sorry for the inconvenience. We ve been listening to your great suggestions and we re working hard to make the app even better. Here s what s new in this release: View all lessons directly on the iPad! Flash is no longer required. New option to clear only the ink on a page leaving images in place. Easily copy the lesson link and embed code. Watch featured lessons from the Educreations community. Optimized recording and uploading. Lessons will now load 4x faster! Logging in and out is now much easier. We fixed a few bugs too.
